{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It's always the other one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] It is true to say that the main [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] source of serious anti-Semitism, pogroms, and so on originated from the north, starting from Lithuania, Latvia, Estonia, Poland, Ukraine underlined three times, Slovakia, Hungary, Croatia, Austria particularly, and southern Germany, Bayern, and especially if you go down to Sudtirol, which is called, which has always been a hotbed of Nazism.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They've got one thing in common.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They are all Catholic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I'm not saying that the Lutherans were particularly favorable to Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But this rampant incitement may not have taken as much place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I remember I had friends who were Protestants.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And maybe it was individual.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But they-- and also maybe because they were also a minority in the country, they were not so-- taking such pleasures to be anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I must say that even in the school as such, I had a perfectly amiable relationship with my school friends.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I remember only one case when there was one boy, who, in fact, didn't even come from that town, he came outside from some rural district, once made a remark.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And even though I knew that they were in the majority, there were some other friends of mine who took my side.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, you see, it's very difficult to explain that you live in a seriously anti-Semitic time, but there are certain signs and events which make you feel to become perfectly complacent that all is well.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It will all pass by.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not all are bad-- which is true.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, of course, the management from the top knew what they were doing, and it was a systematic way to drive in the direction which led to the Holocaust, basically.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
